body_html:
Are you running on the same system you built TF on?
Ubuntu 17.04 should have a much more recent version of gcc, but this line in your python output is confusing:

[GCC 4.4.7 20120313 (Red Hat 4.4.7-1)] on linux

That is quite an old GCC version. Maybe the python coming with Anaconda is the problem. Did you try installing python through Ubuntu package manager?

body:
Are you running on the same system you built TF on?
Ubuntu 17.04 should have a much more recent version of gcc, but this line in your python output is confusing:
```
[GCC 4.4.7 20120313 (Red Hat 4.4.7-1)] on linux
```
That is quite an old GCC version. Maybe the python coming with Anaconda is the problem. Did you try installing python through Ubuntu package manager?
